## Legend

| Symbol | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| Cell `high (Δhigh)` | High-risk pair — strong coupling, very different change rates |
| Cell `high (Δlow)` | Tight pair that co-evolves — possibly one BC, not two |
| Cell `low (Δhigh)` | Healthy decoupling — BCs evolve independently |
| Cell `—` | Diagonal or no coupling |
| 🟥 BC node | High volatility — changes frequently |
| 🟧 BC node | Medium volatility |
| 🟢 BC node | Low volatility — stable |
| `===` edge | High-coupling relationship (shown only for high-strength pairs) |

